The HD 83443 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 83443 is a star with 0.79 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.94 times its radius. It is located 133.56 light years away from the solar system.

HD 83443 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 83443 system


HD 83443 b

HD 83443 b was discovered by the Multiple Observatories observatory using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.04 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 83443 b is 108.12 times the mass of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 83443 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
